title: Need Asana Expert to Set up Optimal Workflow System for Growing Digital Marketing Company
description:
Digital content creation company and personal brand that needs help setting up Asana in the best way possible for our workflow.

What we do:

Our clients meet us for 1 hour per month for a podcast style interview, and we then take that content and send to our video editors and content creators so our clients get 30+ pieces of ready to post social media content. 

Here's what we need:

1. We will tell you everything about what we deliver to clients, and communicate the clear vision of the way we want to be able to manage our projects
2. Based on the information we provide, you would recommend and create the most optimal setup in our Asana account
3. Once complete - you would help train our team (on a few zoom calls) on how to best interact and use the system. We want to know best practices.
4. Help us integrate Asana into our day to day operations and tools (i.e. Slack integration, gmail, etc)

Requirements 

- Expert knowledge of Asana. We don't have time to train you on the tool. 
- Experience working with digital marketing/content marketing workflows
- Eastern or Central Time Zone USA
- Comfortable taking a leadership role in training the owner and our small team
- Familiarity with using Slack

We are growing fast, and are looking for someone who thrives in that environment. 

HOW TO APPLY:

Please attach TWO separate .pdf files. One file for your resume or relevant experience, and one file with a short cover letter telling us why you're excited about this gig

title: Online fitness and nutrition coach to help me get in better shape
description:
I'm looking for an online nutrition and fitness coach to help me eat healthier, exercise more frequently/intensely/longer and keep me accountable so I get in much better shape and get painfree.

I'd like to eat cleaner and optimal for muscle gain. I'd like to gain 10 kg of muscles. I'd like to have lots more energy and sleep better too.

I'd also like to become mentally tougher and build more self-discipline as a consequence of eating clean and exercising consistently. Improving sleep and daily habits is also a goal of mine and I need you to keep me accountable and react if I dont follow our plan.

I'd like to get painfree, as I have some problems with my heels, shoulder and elbow. And I'd like you to focus on keeping me painfree all the time.

I'd like to follow an sustainable exercise program. For nutrition, I'd like to figure out a sustainable clean eating style.

I'd like to have short daily check ins (could be text via Whatsapp) to keep me accountable and perhaps one longer (30-60 minutes) Zoom video meeting once a week to review, tweak, optimize, and plan.

Here are also some optional things I'm entertaining but haven't committed to yet. These ideas below are just me brainstorming.
I'm also happy to video record me doing exercises (and send it to you) so you can give me feedback.  I can also send you pictures of everything I eat for you to review and me to stay accountable.

If you hare a physical therapist og have any other degree around getting and staying painfree it is a big plus. Please include the name alex in your application. If you dont have such agree it may also be ok.

title: Formulation Scientist - Dietary Supplements
description:
Are you passionate about improving people's health through innovative dietary supplements? We are seeking a skilled and experienced Formulation Scientist to join our dynamic team and create cutting-edge formulas for our line of women's health-focused food supplements.

Responsibilities:

- Conduct in-depth research on ingredients to be included in the supplement formulations, considering scientific literature, clinical studies, branded ingredients and safety data.
- Develop safe and effective formulations for each product in our women's health supplement line, addressing specific health concerns and utilizing branded ingredients where applicable.
- Collaborate with the Product Development team to ensure that the formulations align with our brand's vision and meet market demands.
- Calculate precise ingredient quantities based on dosages recommended in scientific literature and adhere to regulatory guidelines.
- Source high-quality ingredients from reputable suppliers, ensuring consistency and purity.
- Collaborate with manufacturing and packaging teams to facilitate product production and labeling accuracy.
- Stay updated with the latest developments in nutritional science, ingredient innovations, and industry trends.
- Work with cross-functional teams to ensure that products meet company standards and customer expectations.
- Maintain comprehensive records of formulation development, ingredient sourcing, and quality assurance protocols.

Optional:
-- Conduct stability and quality control tests to ensure the integrity and efficacy of the formulations.


Requirements:

- Bachelor's or Master's degree in Nutrition, Food Science, Pharmaceutical Sciences, or related fields.
- Proven experience as a Formulation Scientist or in a similar role, ideally within the dietary supplements industry.
- In-depth knowledge of nutritional science, dietary supplements, and regulatory guidelines.
- Familiarity with branded ingredients and their applications in supplement development.
- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to interpret scientific data and make data-driven decisions.
- Excellent attention to detail and accuracy in ingredient calculations.
- Effective communication and teamwork skills to collaborate with various departments.
- Ability to multitask and prioritize projects in a fast-paced environment.
- Demonstrated passion for promoting women's health and well-being.
- Ethical and safety-conscious approach to product development.

Join our team and contribute to the creation of innovative women's health supplements that empower individuals to lead healthier lives. We offer a competitive salary, benefits package, and the opportunity to work in a collaborative and forward-thinking environment.

To apply, please write "MOJO" on top of your application along with your resume, cover letter, and any relevant certifications or portfolio showcasing your past formulation projects if possible. We look forward to receiving your application!
